llan-says-goodbye-to-the-time-lord-8157215.html|title=Dr Who? Gillan says goodbye to the Time Lord|last=McLean|first=Craig|date=23 September 2012|work=[[The Independent]]|quote=Indeed, a few days later, the Daily Mail will insinuate \u2013 via a huge and fragrant front-page portrait of the actress, then another photograph inside of the pair attending a Celtic match \u2013 that she has \"fallen\" for her co-star.|accessdate=9 August 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Bobby Gillespie]], lead singer of [[Primal Scream]]<ref name=\"McGee\"/>\n* [[Clare Grogan]], actress and singer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.celticfc.net/news/15331|title=Clare Grogan: Celtic has always been part of my life|author=Newsroom Staff|website=www.celticfc.net|accessdate=9 February 2020}}</ref>\n* [[John Higgins (snooker player)|John Higgins]], snooker player<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/snooker/43943360 |title=Double joy for Celtic fan John Higgins as Rangers and Jack Lisowski are thrashed |work=BBC Sport|date=29 April 2018|accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Jay Z]], American rapper<ref>{{cite news|url=https://twitter.com/celticcelebrity/status/780194603983142912?lang=en|title= Jay-Z. Rapper & Husband to Beyonc\u00e9|date=25 September 2016|work=[[twitter]]|accessdate=9 August 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Robbie Keane]], Irish footballer<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/celtic-move-fulfils-robbie-keanes-boyhood-dream-6739286.html|title=Celtic move fulfils Robbie Keane's boyhood dream|date=1 February 2010|work=[[Evening Standard]]|accessdate=25 August 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Michelle Keegan]], English actress<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.scotlandnow.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/michelle-keegan-puts-visit-celtic-4831899|title=Michelle Keegan puts visit to Celtic Park at top of her list of New Year resolutions - Scotland Now|first=Scotland|last=Now|website=www.scotlandnow.dailyrecord.co.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Jim Kerr]], lead singer and founding member of [[Simple Minds]]<ref>{{cite news|ur