}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2007\u201308 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2007\u201308]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2007\u201308 Memphis Tigers men's basketball team|Memphis]]\n| 40 || 40 || 29.2 || .477 || .337 || .712 || 4.5 || 4.7 || 1.2 || .4 || 14.9\n{{S-end}}\n\n==Accomplishments and awards==\n\n===NBA===\n* '''NBA Most Valuable Player''': 2011<ref name=\"NBA.com\"/>\n* '''NBA All-Star Selection''': 2010,<ref>[http://www.nba.com/2010/allstar/2010/01/28/reserves.release/index.html NBA.com: Nowitzki leads parade of reserves to Dallas<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100131181722/http://www.nba.com/2010/allstar/2010/01/28/reserves.release/index.html |date=January 31, 2010 }}</ref> 2011,<ref name=autogenerated1 /> 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/chicago/nba/story/_/id/7534419/2012-nba-all-star-game-miami-heat-los-angeles-teams-fill-all-star-starters|title=Heat, LA teams fill All-Star starting rosters|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''All-NBA First Team''': 2011<ref name=\"ant\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/2011/news/05/12/all-nba-release/index.html|title=LeBron James, Derrick Rose highlight 2010\u201311 All-NBA squad|date=May 12, 2011|work=NBA.com|accessdate=May 12, 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514194754/http://www.nba.com/2011/news/05/12/all-nba-release/index.html|archivedate=May 14, 2011}}</ref>\n* '''NBA Rookie of the Year''': 2009<ref name=\"Rookie of the Year\" />\n* '''NBA All-Rookie First Team''': 2009<ref name=\"All-Rookie Team\" />\n* '''Skills Challenge Champion''': 2009\n* '''Conference Rookie of the Month''': November, December, March<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/awards/rom.html|title=NBA Rookies of the Month - Basketball-Reference.com|website=Basketball-Reference.com}}</ref>\n* '''Conference Player of the Month''': April 2010, March 2011<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/awards/pom.html|title=NBA Players of the Month - Basketball-Reference.com|website=Basketball-Reference.com}}</ref>\n\n===College===\n*'''Freshman year (2007\u201308)'''\n** NCAA Tournament All-Final Four Team<ref name=\"allffteam\" />\n** NCAA Tournament South Region MVP<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Sports/wireStory?id=4551903|title=Memphis Rolls Past Texas Into Final Four|author=Jaime Aron|publisher=ABC News|date=March 30, 2008|accessdate=January 29, 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080402002508/http://abcnews.go.com/Sports/wireStory?id=4551903|archivedate=April 2, 2008}}</ref>\n** [[National Association of Basketball Coaches|NABC]] 3rd Team All-American<ref name=\"3rd Team All-American\" />\n**NABC All-District 7 First Team\n**All-[[Conference USA]] First Team<ref name=\"awards\">{{cite web|author=Information|url=http://conferenceusa.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/062608aaf.html|title=Memphis' Derrick Rose Selected No. 1 In 2008 NBA Draft By Chicago Bulls|website=conferenceusa.cstv.com/|publisher=Conference USA Official Athletic Website|date=April 6, 2008|accessdate=June 27, 2008}}</ref>\n** [[Conference USA]] Freshman of the Year<ref name=\"awards\" />\n**Conference USA All Freshman Team 1st Team<ref name=\"awards\" />\n**Sporting News All-Freshman Team<ref name=\"Sporting News All-Freshman\">{{cite web|url=http://gotigersgo.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/031208aac.html|title=Douglas-Roberts Named To Sporting News, Sports Illustrated All-America teams|website=gotigersgo.cstv.com|publisher=Memphis Tigers Official Athletic Website|date=March 12, 2008|accessdate=January 13, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080515194832/http://gotigersgo.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/031208aac.html|archive-date=May 15, 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n**Conference USA Player of the Week for games between December 17 through the 23rd<ref name=\"1207pow\">{{cite web|title=Douglas-Roberts Named To Sporting News, Sports Illustrated All-America teams